and two days.

66
00:07:52,221 --> 00:07:54,394
It is the custom.

67
00:07:54,557 --> 00:07:56,810
I wonder what you
will do without me.

68
00:07:57,644 --> 00:07:59,612
I won't stay idle.

69
00:08:01,064 --> 00:08:03,237
Darling, it's good money.

70
00:08:05,317 --> 00:08:08,572
If only I didn't have to share
your cooking with other people.

71
00:08:10,072 --> 00:08:11,995
You don't.

72
00:08:16,245 --> 00:08:17,305
(GRUNTS)

73
00:08:17,329 --> 00:08:19,923
Be good for your mother.
Okay, Alonzo?

74
00:08:21,668 --> 00:08:23,920
Can I get a kiss, please?
Thank you.

75
00:08:24,586 --> 00:08:25,588
Travel safely.

76
00:08:25,754 --> 00:08:27,177
Stay safely.

77
00:08:30,593 --> 00:08:31,764
Ready?

78
00:08:31,886 --> 00:08:33,011
(DRIVER URGING HORSES)

79
00:08:40,227 --> 00:08:41,855
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)
(BELLS TOLLING)

80
00:08:47,245 --> 00:08:49,086
MR. MOON: Devil call his
name, there he is now.

81
00:08:49,111 --> 00:08:50,455
Mr. Northup!

82
00:08:50,613 --> 00:08:53,331
I have two gentlemen whose
acquaintance you should make.

83
00:08:53,490 --> 00:08:55,493
Misters Brown and Hamilton.

84
00:08:55,659 --> 00:08:56,786
Sir.

85
00:08:56,952 --> 00:08:58,796
Mr. Northup,
these two gentlemen...

86
00:08:58,955 --> 00:09:01,378
were inquiring about
distinguished individuals...

87
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:03,214
and I was just
this very moment...

88
00:09:03,375 --> 00:09:06,549
saying Solomon Northup is an
expert player on the violin.

89
00:09:06,712 --> 00:09:07,884
He was indeed.

90
00:09:08,005 --> 00:09:09,131
Mr. Moon is being
overly gracious.

91
00:09:09,298 --> 00:09:10,676
Well, taking into consideration

92
00:09:10,799 --> 00:09:12,221
his graciousness
and your modesty...

93
00:09:12,384 --> 00:09:15,389
may we trouble you for a moment
of your time to converse, sir?

94
00:09:15,554 --> 00:09:16,807
Of course.

95
00:09:17,222 --> 00:09:18,349
Good day.

96
00:09:18,682 --> 00:09:19,980
SOLOMON: <i>A circus?</i>

97
00:09:20,143 --> 00:09:21,286
That is our usual employee.

98
00:09:21,311 --> 00:09:22,857
The company currently
in the city of Washington.

99
00:09:23,020 --> 00:09:24,739
Circus is too
constricting a word...

100
00:09:24,898 --> 00:09:27,400
to describe the talented and
merry band with which we travel.

101
00:09:27,567 --> 00:09:30,490
It is a spectacle unlike
most have ever witnessed.

102
00:09:30,653 --> 00:09:32,326
Creatures from
the darkest Africa

103
00:09:32,447 --> 00:09:34,073
as yet unseen by civilized man.

104
00:09:34,365 --> 00:09:35,662
Acrobats from the Orient...

105
00:09:35,825 --> 00:09:38,845
who contort themselves in the
most confounding manners.

106
00:09:38,870 --> 00:09:40,871
(LAUGHS) And I myself
in aide of Mr. Brown...

107
00:09:41,038 --> 00:09:42,711
an internationally
renowned practitioner

108
00:09:42,831 --> 00:09:44,549
in the art of prestidigitation.

109
00:09:44,709 --> 00:09:46,086
We are on our way
thither to rejoin

110
00:09:46,211 --> 00:09:47,587
the company having left
for a short time...

111
00:09:47,754 --> 00:09:49,881
to make a small profit from
our own exhibitions.

112
00:09:50,048 --> 00:09:51,727
The reason for our inquiry
with Mr. Moon...

113
00:09:51,883 --> 00:09:53,634
Yes. We had just
a devil of a time

114
00:09:53,759 --> 00:09:55,511
in procuring music
for our entertainments.

115
00:09:55,677 --> 00:09:57,679
Men of true talents are
seemingly in short supply.

116
00:09:57,846 --> 00:09:58,847
Thank you, sir.

117
00:09:59,014 --> 00:10:01,938
If we could persuade you to
accompany us as far as Washington-

118
00:10:02,101 --> 00:10:04,524
We could give you one dollar
for each day's services...

119
00:10:04,687 --> 00:10:07,086
and three dollars for every night
played at our performances.

120
00:10:07,190 --> 00:10:09,083
In addition, we would
provide sufficient pay...

121
00:10:09,109 --> 00:10:12,203
for your return here to
Saratoga, two weeks from today.

122
00:10:17,366 --> 00:10:19,620
Welcome to Washington, Solomon.

123
00:10:20,245 --> 00:10:22,121
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

124
00:10:25,625 --> 00:10:27,184
(ALL LAUGHING)

125
00:10:27,210 --> 00:10:29,428
Hamilton, you know too much.

126
00:10:29,586 --> 00:10:31,088
Some say not enough.

127
00:10:31,548 --> 00:10:34,972
Solomon, 43 dollars.
All to you.

128
00:10:36,094 --> 00:10:38,062
That is far more
than my wages amount to.

129
00:10:38,221 --> 00:10:39,768
BROWN: It's been a most
profitable week, sir.

130
00:10:39,972 --> 00:10:41,225
Cheers.
Cheers.

131
00:10:41,390 --> 00:10:42,607
Cheers.

132
00:10:47,230 --> 00:10:48,731
Another.

133
00:10:50,274 --> 00:10:55,280
Gentlemen, your generosity
is extraordinary.

134
00:10:55,446 --> 00:10:57,494
And your talents are undeniable.

135
00:10:57,657 --> 00:10:58,703
Mmm. To Solomon.

136
00:10:58,866 --> 00:11:01,370
Cheers.

137
00:11:12,004 --> 00:11:13,256
(CHAINS RATTLING)

138
00:11:22,764 --> 00:11:24,607
(RATTLING CONTINUES)

139
00:11:41,868 --> 00:11:43,620
Ugh!
(GROANING)

140
00:11:45,038 --> 00:11:46,664
It's all right, Solomon.

141
00:11:46,831 --> 00:11:47,956
There's no shame in it.

142
00:11:48,124 --> 00:11:49,546
No shame at all.

143
00:11:59,719 --> 00:12:01,096
(GRUNTING)

144
00:12:11,397 --> 00:12:13,517
(WHISPERS) Hamilton, we must hurry.
(SOLOMON GROANING)

145
00:12:14,274 --> 00:12:15,460
One too many libation.

146
00:12:15,485 --> 00:12:16,836
(SOLOMON COUGHS)
We're halfway there.

147
00:12:16,860 --> 00:12:18,238
(CHAINS RATTLING LOUDLY)

148
00:12:21,448 --> 00:12:22,826
(GRUNTING)

149
00:12:30,667 --> 00:12:31,918
(PANTING)

150
00:12:33,753 --> 00:12:35,104
SOLOMON: <i>So sorry...</i>

151
00:12:35,129 --> 00:12:36,272
(SHUSHING)

152
00:12:36,297 --> 00:12:38,139
We won't hear it. We won't.

153
00:12:38,298 --> 00:12:40,317
Let him sleep, Hamilton.

154
00:12:40,342 --> 00:12:42,892
Mmm.
A good night's rest.

155
00:12:43,428 --> 00:12:45,147
And tomorrow...

156
00:12:46,224 --> 00:12:48,522
tomorrow you will feel
as well and refreshed

157
00:12:48,643 --> 00:12:50,895
as if the earth were new again.

158
00:12:51,062 --> 00:12:53,815
(SCOFFS) Hamilton, there's
nothing more we can do for him.

159
00:12:55,607 --> 00:12:57,000
Such is the pity.

160
00:12:57,025 --> 00:12:58,369
(BLOWING)

161
00:13:00,363 --> 00:13:01,534
(GASPING)

162
00:13:04,158 --> 00:13:05,500
(DOOR OPENS)

163
00:13:06,451 --> 00:13:09,331
Well, boy, how do you feel now?

164
00:13:11,666 --> 00:13:15,591
My name... My name
is Solomon Northup.

165
00:13:15,753 --> 00:13:19,006
I'm a free man. A resident
of Saratoga, New York.

166
00:13:19,173 --> 00:13:21,801
The residence of my wife and
children who are equally free.

167
00:13:21,967 --> 00:13:23,845
And you have no right
whatsoever to detain me.

168
00:13:24,011 --> 00:13:25,389
You're not any free man.

169
00:13:25,554 --> 00:13:26,851
And I promise you...

170
00:13:27,014 --> 00:13:29,187
I promise you upon my liberation

171
00:13:29,308 --> 00:13:31,481
I will have satisfaction
for this wrong.

172
00:13:33,145 --> 00:13:34,614
Resolve this.

173
00:13:35,023 --> 00:13:36,570
Produce your papers.

174
00:13:44,490 --> 00:13:46,241
You're no free man.

175
00:13:46,908 --> 00:13:48,831
And you ain't from Saratoga.

176
00:13:49,370 --> 00:13:51,246
You're from Georgia.

177
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:56,503
You ain't a free man.

178
00:13:58,337 --> 00:14:02,388
You're nothing but
a Georgia runaway.

179
00:14:04,469 --> 00:14:09,100
You're just a runaway nigger...

180
00:14:09,639 --> 00:14:11,517
from Georgia.

181
00:14:27,825 --> 00:14:29,326
(GRUNTS)
(GROANS)

182
00:14:29,994 --> 00:14:31,291
(PANTING)

183
00:14:34,790 --> 00:14:36,087
(GROANING)

184
00:14:42,798 --> 00:14:44,471
You're a slave!

185
00:14:44,966 --> 00:14:47,611
You're a Georgia slave!

186
00:14:47,636 --> 00:14:49,105
(SCREAMING)

187
00:14:51,139 --> 00:14:52,642
(PANTING)

188
00:15:04,361 --> 00:15:06,034
Are you a slave?

189
00:15:07,322 --> 00:15:08,495
No.

190
00:15:11,827 --> 00:15:13,000
(GROANING)

191
00:15:23,004 --> 00:15:24,315
(GRUNTING)

192
00:15:24,340 --> 00:15:26,558
(SOBBING IN PAIN)

193
00:15:34,015 --> 00:15:36,313
(GASPING)

194
00:15:52,368 --> 00:15:53,539
(DOOR CLOSES)
(LOCK CLICKS)

195
00:15:54,495 --> 00:15:56,121
(SOLOMON GROANING)

196
00:15:58,124 --> 00:16:00,047
(CHAINS RATTLING)

197
00:16:06,548 --> 00:16:08,051
SOLOMON: (SOBBING) Help.

198
00:16:09,302 --> 00:16:11,019
Help me.

199
00:16:12,388 --> 00:16:14,186
Help me!

200
00:16:14,849 --> 00:16:17,226
Somebody help me!

201
00:16:17,934 --> 00:16:20,062
Help!

202
00:16:21,855 --> 00:16:23,357
Help!

203
00:16:28,361 --> 00:16:29,705
(DOOR OPENS)

204
00:16:35,076 --> 00:16:37,875
That old thing of yours
is just rags and tatters.

205
00:16:38,038 --> 00:16:40,508
You need something
proper to wear.

206
00:16:43,586 --> 00:16:45,884
Go on, put it on.

207
00:17:05,232 --> 00:17:06,576
There.

208
00:17:09,903 --> 00:17:11,326
That's fine.

209
00:17:11,780 --> 00:17:13,703
That's fine.

210
00:17:15,951 --> 00:17:17,077
Got no gratitude?

211
00:17:22,500 --> 00:17:23,500
No. That's from my wife.

212
00:17:23,667 --> 00:17:25,214
Rags and tatters.

213
00:17:25,461 --> 00:17:27,884
Rags and tatters.

214
00:17:29,923 --> 00:17:31,267
(DOOR CLOSES)

215
00:17:37,890 --> 00:17:39,642
Go on, wash up.

216
00:17:42,519 --> 00:17:44,363
The boy, too.
Get him clean.

217
00:17:47,023 --> 00:17:48,401
Scrub now.

218
00:17:48,567 --> 00:17:50,740
Do you know when
my mama will come?

219
00:17:51,237 --> 00:17:52,296
Hush him up!

220
00:17:52,320 --> 00:17:53,322
Mama! Mama!

221
00:17:53,489 --> 00:17:54,490
Quiet.

222
00:17:54,781 --> 00:17:56,125
Quiet, please.
Mama!

223
00:17:56,284 --> 00:17:57,410
Hush him up!

224
00:17:57,576 --> 00:18:00,955
Your mother will come, I swear she will.
But you must be silent.

225
00:18:01,538 --> 00:18:03,007
Be silent.

226
00:18:10,088 --> 00:18:11,606
We need a sympathetic ear.

227
00:18:11,632 --> 00:18:12,692
(RANDALL HUMMING)

228
00:18:12,717 --> 00:18:14,469
An opportunity to
explain our situation.

229
00:18:14,634 --> 00:18:16,636
Who, in your estimation,
is that sympathetic ear?

230
00:18:16,804 --> 00:18:18,521
The two men I journeyed with.

231
00:18:18,681 --> 00:18:20,557
I'm certain they're making
enquiries at this very moment.

232
00:18:20,724 --> 00:18:22,067
I'd be just as
certain they're counting

233
00:18:22,183 --> 00:18:23,527
the money paid for delivering
you to this place.

234
00:18:23,685 --> 00:18:26,734
They were not kidnappers, they
were artists. Fellow performers.

235
00:18:26,896 --> 00:18:28,365
You know that?

236
00:18:28,523 --> 00:18:30,526
You know for certain
who they were?

237
00:18:32,193 --> 00:18:36,369
The reality to come is us
being transported southward.

238
00:18:36,531 --> 00:18:38,625
New Orleans,
if I was to venture.

239
00:18:39,367 --> 00:18:41,746
After we arrive,
we'll be put to market.

240
00:18:41,912 --> 00:18:43,538
And beyond that...

241
00:18:44,414 --> 00:18:46,934
Well, I suppose once in a slave
state, there's only one outcome.

242
00:18:47,042 --> 00:18:47,713
No.

243
00:18:47,876 --> 00:18:49,876
I don't say that to give
you empty agitation, John.

244
00:18:49,878 --> 00:18:51,631
For y'all, there ain't
nothing but that.

245
00:18:51,797 --> 00:18:53,265
But John wasn't kidnapped.

246
00:18:53,423 --> 00:18:55,846
John's just being held
as debt, that's all.

247
00:18:56,009 --> 00:18:57,932
Master pay his debt
and John be redeemed.

248
00:18:58,095 --> 00:18:59,575
Boy, our masters
will not come for us.

249
00:18:59,721 --> 00:19:01,723
John is sorry for y'all,
but that's how it be.

250
00:19:01,891 --> 00:19:03,733
Where you're going,
you're going without John.

251
00:19:05,769 --> 00:19:07,113
RANDALL: Mama!
Randall!

252
00:19:08,605 --> 00:19:09,857
Mama!

253
00:19:11,608 --> 00:19:13,406
Are you all right?

254
00:19:14,028 --> 00:19:15,450
Are you all right?

255
00:19:17,280 --> 00:19:18,702
Thank you, God.

256
00:19:20,534 --> 00:19:22,411
(DOOR OPENS)
Come on. Get up.

257
00:19:22,744 --> 00:19:24,291
I said, get up!
ELIZA: No, don't...

258
00:19:24,454 --> 00:19:26,377
I don't want to hear you talk!
Get in the yard.

259
00:19:26,539 --> 00:19:27,586
Not my children!

260
00:19:27,750 --> 00:19:31,095
Ain't no need for all that. Just
taking a little trip, that's all.

261
00:19:31,753 --> 00:19:33,346
Don't want to
frighten the children

262
00:19:33,463 --> 00:19:35,090
over a little boat ride, do you?

263
00:19:35,257 --> 00:19:36,930
John's master
gonna pay his debt.

264
00:19:37,093 --> 00:19:38,094
Line up!

265
00:19:38,219 --> 00:19:39,444
His master gonna pay his debt!

266
00:19:39,470 --> 00:19:41,096
(JOHN GROANING)

267
00:19:45,267 --> 00:19:47,941
I don't want to hear a word
out of none of you!

268
00:19:48,938 --> 00:19:50,280
Not a one.

269
00:20:03,411 --> 00:20:04,878
All right, come on.

270
00:20:06,413 --> 00:20:08,290
Move.
Come on.

271
00:20:09,875 --> 00:20:11,376
Come on, child.
Come on.

272
00:20:11,544 --> 00:20:13,046
Follow your mama.

273
00:20:13,211 --> 00:20:14,270
Come on, boy.

274
00:20:14,296 --> 00:20:15,355
RADBURN: Up these stairs.

275
00:20:15,381 --> 00:20:17,634
BURCH: Get down out
of that wagon. Come on.

276
00:20:18,259 --> 00:20:19,635
Come on. Move it!

277
00:20:20,135 --> 00:20:21,479
Let's go!

278
00:20:21,636 --> 00:20:22,980
Up, up, up the stairs.

279
00:20:24,222 --> 00:20:25,769
Come on, let's go.

280
00:20:30,270 --> 00:20:31,772
Come on, move it!

281
00:20:32,064 --> 00:20:33,691
All right, come on.

282
00:20:35,567 --> 00:20:37,740
RADBURN: Hey, you.
Get up.

283
00:20:38,069 --> 00:20:39,822
Sit down, right there.

284
00:20:40,114 --> 00:20:41,536
(BURCH LAUGHING)

285
00:20:42,324 --> 00:20:43,165
Come on.

286
00:20:44,910 --> 00:20:46,583
Right there. Just sit down.

287
00:21:22,865 --> 00:21:25,084
Cheer up and
don't be so cast down.

288
00:21:30,538 --> 00:21:31,756
(DOOR SLAMS)

289
00:21:35,126 --> 00:21:39,427
If you want to survive, do and
say as little as possible.

290
00:21:40,758 --> 00:21:45,137
Tell no one who you really are and
tell no one you can read and write.

291
00:21:47,222 --> 00:21:50,241
Unless you want to
be a dead nigger.

292
00:21:50,267 --> 00:21:51,689
(DOOR OPENS)

293
00:22:05,740 --> 00:22:07,334
MAN: Now keep
your mouth shut.

294
00:22:15,084 --> 00:22:16,926
I say we fight.

295
00:22:17,920 --> 00:22:19,422
The crew is fairly small.

296
00:22:20,256 --> 00:22:22,607
Were it well planned, I believe
they could be strong-armed.

297
00:22:22,633 --> 00:22:24,509
Three can't go
against the whole crew.

298
00:22:25,635 --> 00:22:27,637
The rest here are niggers.

299
00:22:27,971 --> 00:22:29,348
Born and bred slaves.

300
00:22:29,515 --> 00:22:31,768
Niggers ain't got
no stomach for a fight.

301
00:22:31,933 --> 00:22:33,277
Not a damn one.

302
00:22:33,434 --> 00:22:37,234
All's I know, if we get
where we're traveling...

303
00:22:37,647 --> 00:22:39,069
we'll wish we'd died trying.

304
00:22:39,232 --> 00:22:41,701
Survival's not
about certain death,

305
00:22:41,818 --> 00:22:44,322
it's about
keeping your head down.

306
00:22:47,282 --> 00:22:50,126
Days ago,
I was with my family...

307
00:22:51,662 --> 00:22:53,460
in my home.

308
00:22:54,999 --> 00:22:57,343
Now you tell me all is lost.

309
00:22:59,461 --> 00:23:02,681
"Tell no one who I am."
That's the way to survive?

310
00:23:05,925 --> 00:23:07,973
Well, I don't want to survive.

311
00:23:09,512 --> 00:23:12,642
I want to live.

312
00:24:11,532 --> 00:24:12,875
(LAUGHS)

313
00:24:14,619 --> 00:24:15,872
(STABS)

314
00:24:22,377 --> 00:24:23,424
(SCREAMING)

315
00:24:41,396 --> 00:24:43,069
Better off.

316
00:24:44,023 --> 00:24:45,570
Better than us.

317
00:25:02,584 --> 00:25:03,836
I don't see him.

318
00:25:04,002 --> 00:25:04,720
Clemens!

319
00:25:05,170 --> 00:25:06,717
Clemens Ray!
Master.

320
00:25:06,880 --> 00:25:08,096
Clemens!
Master Ray, sir!

321
00:25:08,257 --> 00:25:09,509
Master Ray!

322
00:25:09,674 --> 00:25:10,796
JONUS: Who's in charge here?

323
00:25:10,925 --> 00:25:11,926
I'm the captain!

324
00:25:12,094 --> 00:25:13,266
I'm Mr. Jonus Ray.

325
00:25:13,429 --> 00:25:15,021
My solicitor has
documentation...

326
00:25:15,180 --> 00:25:17,932
verifying the negro known as
Clemens Ray is my property.

327
00:25:18,099 --> 00:25:20,443
I know nothing of
this arrangement.

328
00:25:20,602 --> 00:25:22,453
JONUS: You are ordered to
return that property

329
00:25:22,479 --> 00:25:24,230
immediately or be
charged with thievery.

330
00:25:25,441 --> 00:25:26,692
Free him!

331
00:25:29,611 --> 00:25:30,737
Master.

332
00:25:30,903 --> 00:25:32,701
Master Ray, sir.

333
00:25:34,115 --> 00:25:35,083
Clemens!

334
00:25:35,241 --> 00:25:36,442
Clemens!
CAPTAIN: Get him back!

335
00:25:36,576 --> 00:25:37,953
Clemens!

336
00:25:38,619 --> 00:25:39,621
Clemens!

337
00:25:40,538 --> 00:25:41,381
Clemens!

338
00:26:11,403 --> 00:26:13,326
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

339
00:26:46,063 --> 00:26:47,359
(SINGING)

340
00:26:47,689 --> 00:26:49,083
Mr. Parker.

341
00:26:49,107 --> 00:26:52,407
Ah, Mr. Northup.
Mrs. Northup.

342
00:26:52,653 --> 00:26:54,701
Solomon, could I interest
you in a new cravat?

343
00:26:54,863 --> 00:26:56,173
Pure silk, by way of the French.

344
00:26:56,198 --> 00:26:58,872
We're in need of a fresh
carryall for my Mrs.'s travels.

345
00:26:59,034 --> 00:26:59,875
Nothing more.

346
00:27:00,035 --> 00:27:01,708
The year has passed already.

347
00:27:01,869 --> 00:27:03,180
Off to work at Sandy Hill again?

348
00:27:03,204 --> 00:27:04,047
I am.

349
00:27:04,205 --> 00:27:05,548
I have just the thing.

350
00:27:05,707 --> 00:27:07,380
Something to suit your style...

351
00:27:07,542 --> 00:27:10,011
and yet sturdy enough
for the 40-mile round trip.

352
00:27:10,170 --> 00:27:11,171
It's beautiful.

353
00:27:11,337 --> 00:27:12,259
At what price?

354
00:27:12,381 --> 00:27:13,347
We will take it.

355
00:27:13,507 --> 00:27:16,635
Children, come see what you
father has just purchased for me.

356
00:27:16,801 --> 00:27:18,304
MR. PARKER: One moment, sir,
and you'll be assisted.

357
00:27:18,470 --> 00:27:20,188
Mr. Parker.
Sir?

358
00:27:20,346 --> 00:27:21,564
If we could discuss the price.

359
00:27:21,722 --> 00:27:23,349
Oh, forgive me, Solomon.
Forgive me, Mrs. Northup.

360
00:27:23,517 --> 00:27:25,565
A customer waits.
Welcome, sir.

361
00:27:25,727 --> 00:27:27,569
SOLOMON: Shop well, sir,
but mind your wallet.

362
00:27:27,729 --> 00:27:29,480
MR. PARKER: Pay no attention
to this gentleman's nonsense.

363
00:27:29,647 --> 00:27:30,740
Jasper!

364
00:27:32,233 --> 00:27:34,031
My regrets for
the intrusion, sir.

365
00:27:34,403 --> 00:27:36,076
SOLOMON: No intrusion.

366
00:27:39,907 --> 00:27:41,375
Good day, sir.

367
00:27:41,868 --> 00:27:43,040
MR. PARKER: Good day.

368
00:27:43,202 --> 00:27:44,921
Jasper, out.

369
00:27:53,087 --> 00:27:55,340
Very good. Very good.

370
00:27:55,715 --> 00:27:58,265
Let's see, here. Eliza!

371
00:27:59,595 --> 00:28:01,893
Stand up when you
hear your name. Eliza.

372
00:28:02,763 --> 00:28:03,605
Lethe!

373
00:28:07,019 --> 00:28:07,690
John.

374
00:28:09,438 --> 00:28:10,690
Oren.

375
00:28:11,940 --> 00:28:13,112
Platt.

376
00:28:16,028 --> 00:28:17,119
Platt.

377
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:21,741
(SIGHS) Stand up.

378
00:28:23,701 --> 00:28:25,124
You fit the description given.

379
00:28:25,287 --> 00:28:26,630
Why didn't you
answer when called?

380
00:28:26,788 --> 00:28:28,039
My name is not Platt.

381
00:28:28,207 --> 00:28:29,048
My name...

382
00:28:31,375 --> 00:28:33,094
Your name is Platt.

383
00:28:35,297 --> 00:28:37,470
Captain, get these niggers
to my cart.

384
00:28:37,965 --> 00:28:39,888
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

385
00:28:50,144 --> 00:28:51,317
Mmm.

386
00:28:56,984 --> 00:28:58,156
(CHUCKLES)

387
00:28:59,613 --> 00:29:00,829
Move.

388
00:29:04,417 --> 00:29:06,178
FREEMAN: I believe I have
something very much

389
00:29:06,202 --> 00:29:07,796
to your liking in the back room.

390
00:29:07,954 --> 00:29:09,673
Follow me, please.

391
00:29:09,830 --> 00:29:12,674
Yes. Now, inspect them
at your leisure...

392
00:29:12,834 --> 00:29:17,681
but I ask you to pay particular
regard to young Ezra here.

393
00:29:17,838 --> 00:29:19,090
Incredibly sound limbs.

394
00:29:19,258 --> 00:29:21,352
I have never seen anything
quite like him.

395
00:29:21,509 --> 00:29:24,354
And this marvelous creature.
Can you believe it? Mmm?

396
00:29:24,512 --> 00:29:26,185
She'll make a fine lady's maid.

397
00:29:26,347 --> 00:29:27,519
Madam? (CHUCKLES)

398
00:29:27,848 --> 00:29:29,521
So, inspect at your leisure.

399
00:29:29,684 --> 00:29:31,982
Take your time.
Help yourself to refreshments.

400
00:29:32,144 --> 00:29:35,148
Gentlemen, what catches
your fancy here? Hmm?

401
00:29:35,648 --> 00:29:36,650
This boy? Yes?

402
00:29:36,817 --> 00:29:38,990
Open your mouth.
Open wider.

403
00:29:39,152 --> 00:29:41,529
Look in there. Never been
sick a day in his life.

404
00:29:41,697 --> 00:29:43,339
And I call particular
attention to Martha.

405
00:29:43,365 --> 00:29:45,834
She is an excellent pastry cook.

406
00:29:45,992 --> 00:29:47,711
Ah, Mr. Ford.

407
00:29:48,161 --> 00:29:50,459
Splendid seeing you, sir.
What catches your fancy?

408
00:29:50,622 --> 00:29:52,670
This lad? He's very brawny.

409
00:29:52,833 --> 00:29:55,644
How much for
the ones Platt and Eliza?

410
00:29:55,669 --> 00:29:57,215
Ah, yes.

411
00:29:57,628 --> 00:29:59,855
A thousand for Platt.
Uh... Oh.

412
00:29:59,881 --> 00:30:02,680
This is a nigger of considerable
talent, I assure you.

413
00:30:02,843 --> 00:30:04,560
700 for Eliza.

414
00:30:04,720 --> 00:30:06,393
My fairest price.

415
00:30:06,721 --> 00:30:07,894
Mmm.

416
00:30:08,723 --> 00:30:09,895
You will accept a note?

417
00:30:10,057 --> 00:30:12,652
Please, sir.
Do not divide my family.

418
00:30:12,810 --> 00:30:14,063
Do not take me unless
you take my children.

419
00:30:14,229 --> 00:30:15,230
Eliza! Quiet!

420
00:30:15,396 --> 00:30:17,116
You will have the most
faithful slave in me.

421
00:30:17,273 --> 00:30:18,616
The most faithful slave
that has ever lived.

422
00:30:18,775 --> 00:30:19,901
But I beg that you
do not separate us.

423
00:30:20,027 --> 00:30:21,074
Your price for the boy?

424
00:30:21,236 --> 00:30:22,578
Eliza! Stop it!

425
00:30:22,738 --> 00:30:23,910
I will give you
something to cry about.

426
00:30:24,071 --> 00:30:26,244
Randall, come forward.
Come, come, come.

427
00:30:26,407 --> 00:30:28,626
Now, do you see
how fit this boy is?

428
00:30:28,785 --> 00:30:30,037
Like ripe fruit.

429
00:30:30,202 --> 00:30:33,082
May I take your stick a moment?
Observe this.

430
00:30:33,248 --> 00:30:35,250
Randall, jump, jump, jump.
Run, run, run.

431
00:30:35,416 --> 00:30:37,589
Very good! Higher.

432
00:30:37,752 --> 00:30:38,878
Now, you see this.

433
00:30:39,046 --> 00:30:42,641
It's very likely he will
grow into a fine beast.

434
00:30:43,884 --> 00:30:45,602
600 for the boy.

435
00:30:45,760 --> 00:30:47,262
Fair and final.

436
00:30:47,887 --> 00:30:49,105
Done.

437
00:30:49,263 --> 00:30:51,607
Superb. A moment, please.

438
00:30:51,767 --> 00:30:53,064
Mr. Ford.

439
00:30:53,268 --> 00:30:54,440
Please.
Eliza!

440
00:30:54,603 --> 00:30:56,413
How much for the little girl?

441
00:30:56,438 --> 00:30:57,529
Ah...

442
00:30:57,939 --> 00:30:59,111
You have no use for her.

443
00:30:59,273 --> 00:31:00,946
One so young will
bring you no profit.

444
00:31:01,108 --> 00:31:02,951
No, no, no.
I cannot sell the girl.

445
00:31:03,111 --> 00:31:06,740
No, there's heaps and piles
of money to be made from her.

446
00:31:06,906 --> 00:31:09,204
She's a beauty.
One of the regular bloods.

447
00:31:09,367 --> 00:31:12,167
None of your thick-lipped, bullet-heated,
cotton-picking niggers, here.

448
00:31:12,287 --> 00:31:14,961
Her child, man.

449
00:31:15,374 --> 00:31:16,125
Please.

450
00:31:16,290 --> 00:31:18,371
For God's sake, are you not
sentimental in the least?

451
00:31:18,376 --> 00:31:21,130
My sentimentality extends
the length of a coin.

452
00:31:21,296 --> 00:31:22,798
God, please.

453
00:31:23,339 --> 00:31:26,719
Now do you take this lot,
Mr. Ford, or do you pass on them?

454
00:31:26,884 --> 00:31:30,480
Please, please.
Please.

455
00:31:30,638 --> 00:31:32,185
I will take
the ones Platt and Eliza.

456
00:31:32,348 --> 00:31:33,349
Sold, Eliza and Platt.

457
00:31:33,517 --> 00:31:34,643
I will not go
without my children!

458
00:31:34,768 --> 00:31:35,859
Goddamn sniveling wench!

459
00:31:36,019 --> 00:31:37,287
You will not take them from me!

460
00:31:37,311 --> 00:31:40,030
God damn you! Get her out of here, Cape!
(CHILDREN SCREAMING)

461
00:31:40,190 --> 00:31:41,907
Please! No! No!

462
00:31:42,067 --> 00:31:43,693
Get her out of here,
god damn it!

463
00:31:43,859 --> 00:31:46,829
Platt, get your fiddle.
Play, play, play something.

464
00:31:46,988 --> 00:31:50,083
I will give you something to cry
about, you goddamned witch!

465
00:31:50,241 --> 00:31:52,414
Get her out of here, Cape!
Out, now!

466
00:31:52,661 --> 00:31:56,039
(PLAYING LIVELY TUNE)
CHILDREN: Mama! Mama! Mama!

467
00:31:56,914 --> 00:31:58,962
Yes.

468
00:31:59,125 --> 00:32:01,845
Mr. Ford, a pleasure.

469
00:32:02,086 --> 00:32:03,759
(CHILDREN CONTINUE SCREAMING)

470
00:32:18,394 --> 00:32:20,692
Did you bring all those niggers?

471
00:32:20,855 --> 00:32:23,108
Two of them?
You got two?

472
00:32:23,525 --> 00:32:24,821
FORD: Mr. Chapin.
(SOBBING)

473
00:32:25,443 --> 00:32:27,913
MISTRESS FORD: This one's crying.
Why is this one crying?

474
00:32:28,070 --> 00:32:29,698
FORD: Separated
from her children.

475
00:32:29,865 --> 00:32:31,287
Oh, clear.
It couldn't be helped.

476
00:32:31,450 --> 00:32:32,701
Poor, poor woman.

477
00:32:32,867 --> 00:32:34,119
Mr. Chapin.
Yes, sir.

478
00:32:34,286 --> 00:32:35,753
Tomorrow, you have
to take these two

479
00:32:35,871 --> 00:32:37,373
up to the mill and
start them working.

480
00:32:37,538 --> 00:32:38,756
For now, make them adequate.

481
00:32:38,914 --> 00:32:40,715
Fix them a meal and have
them rest themselves.

482
00:32:40,875 --> 00:32:42,048
Yes, sir.

483
00:32:42,961 --> 00:32:44,177
Come on, now.

484
00:32:44,712 --> 00:32:46,885
Come on! Don't dawdle!

485
00:32:47,173 --> 00:32:49,801
Something to eat, and some rest.

486
00:32:49,968 --> 00:32:51,407
Your children will
soon be forgotten.

487
00:33:18,872 --> 00:33:21,000
For all of you raw niggers
that don't know...

488
00:33:21,165 --> 00:33:25,546
my name is John Tibeats, William
Ford's chief carpenter.

489
00:33:25,711 --> 00:33:29,090
You will refer
to me as "Master."

490
00:33:29,257 --> 00:33:32,978
Mr. Chapin is the overseer
on this plantation.

491
00:33:33,135 --> 00:33:37,686
You, too, will refer
to him as "Master."

492
00:33:38,807 --> 00:33:40,730
So, clap your hands.

493
00:33:44,271 --> 00:33:46,990
Like this. Come on.

494
00:33:47,817 --> 00:33:50,115
Come on, now.
Clap your hands.

