00:35:00,181 --> 00:35:02,353
<i>Run, nigger, run
Well, you better get away</i>

520
00:35:02,516 --> 00:35:04,690
<i>Run, nigger, run
The pattyroller will get you</i>

521
00:35:04,853 --> 00:35:06,855
<i>Run, nigger, run
Well, you better get away</i>

522
00:35:07,355 --> 00:35:10,153
"I am the God of Abraham,
the God of Isaac..."

523
00:35:10,317 --> 00:35:12,657
"and the God of Jacob."

524
00:35:12,682 --> 00:35:14,003
(<i>RUN NIGGER RUN</i>
CONTINUES PLAYING)

525
00:35:14,028 --> 00:35:15,530
"And when
the multitude heard this,"

526
00:35:15,697 --> 00:35:18,371
"they were astonished
at his doctrine."

527
00:35:19,199 --> 00:35:22,170
"And then one of them,
which was a lawyer..."

528
00:35:22,329 --> 00:35:25,548
"asked him a question,
tempting him."

529
00:35:47,728 --> 00:35:49,072
(MEN WHOOPING)

530
00:35:55,820 --> 00:35:57,242
(PLAYING RHYTHMIC TUNE)

531
00:36:01,242 --> 00:36:03,164
(WHOOPING CONTINUES)

532
00:36:21,471 --> 00:36:23,768
SOLOMON: <i>The creek is
plenty deep enough to sail.</i>

533
00:36:24,391 --> 00:36:26,485
Even with a boat full of load.

534
00:36:26,603 --> 00:36:27,842
The distance from the work area

535
00:36:27,851 --> 00:36:28,943
to the point on
the latter bayou...

536
00:36:29,103 --> 00:36:30,822
is several miles by water
fewer than land.

537
00:36:30,980 --> 00:36:32,527
It occurs to me that
the expense of transportation

538
00:36:32,648 --> 00:36:34,242
would be
materially diminished...

539
00:36:34,400 --> 00:36:35,447
"Materially diminished"?

540
00:36:35,610 --> 00:36:37,577
...if we use
the waterway.

541
00:36:37,737 --> 00:36:40,489
Are you an engineer,
or a nigger?

542
00:36:42,784 --> 00:36:45,286
Are you an engineer,
or a nigger?

543
00:36:46,579 --> 00:36:47,626
Let the man say his piece.

544
00:36:47,789 --> 00:36:51,463
It's a scheme. Plenty of engineers
have schemed similarly.

545
00:36:51,626 --> 00:36:54,175
The passes are too tight.

546
00:36:54,628 --> 00:36:57,632
I reckon them at more than 12
feet at their most narrow.

547
00:36:57,798 --> 00:36:59,300
Wide enough for
a tub to traverse

548
00:36:59,425 --> 00:37:00,847
if a team of niggers
cleared it out.

549
00:37:01,010 --> 00:37:03,762
And you know what of
transport and terraforming?

550
00:37:03,929 --> 00:37:05,648
I labored repairing
the Champlain canal...

551
00:37:05,806 --> 00:37:09,152
on the section over which William
van Nortwick was superintendent.

552
00:37:09,309 --> 00:37:12,188
With my earnings, I hired several
efficient hands to assist me...

553
00:37:12,355 --> 00:37:13,652
and entered into contracts for

554
00:37:13,773 --> 00:37:15,070
the transportation of
large rafts of timber...

555
00:37:15,233 --> 00:37:17,702
from Lake Champlain to Troy.

556
00:37:20,237 --> 00:37:23,492
Well, I'll admit to being
impressed even if you won't.

557
00:37:24,534 --> 00:37:26,581
Collect a team. See
what good you can do.

558
00:37:32,166 --> 00:37:33,793
(SLAVES SINGING)

559
00:37:35,670 --> 00:37:36,922
You good? Clear it out!

560
00:37:37,088 --> 00:37:38,356
Two, three...

561
00:37:38,380 --> 00:37:39,597
(BOTH GRUNTING)

562
00:37:41,509 --> 00:37:44,353
SLAVES: (SINGING)
<i>Too late for me</i>

563
00:37:44,512 --> 00:37:47,561
<i>I live or die</i>

564
00:37:47,724 --> 00:37:50,853
<i>Lay down and cry</i>

565
00:37:51,018 --> 00:37:54,114
<i>Hey, boy
I'm tired</i>

566
00:37:54,271 --> 00:37:57,367
<i>My lord
Sometimes</i>

567
00:37:57,525 --> 00:38:00,778
<i>I'm strong
Yes, sir</i>

568
00:38:00,945 --> 00:38:04,324
<i>I'm tall
Yes, sir</i>

569
00:38:05,074 --> 00:38:06,746
(APPLAUDING)

570
00:38:10,079 --> 00:38:12,297
Platt, you are a marvel.

571
00:38:13,333 --> 00:38:14,880
(GRUNTING)

572
00:38:19,963 --> 00:38:21,681
What took you so long?
(CHUCKLES)

573
00:38:22,257 --> 00:38:24,306
Thank you, Master Ford.

574
00:38:25,552 --> 00:38:27,054
(ALL CONGRATULATING)

575
00:38:31,059 --> 00:38:32,231
(WHOOPING)

576
00:38:41,860 --> 00:38:43,204
FORD: Platt.

577
00:38:54,666 --> 00:38:55,963
(SIGHS)

578
00:39:02,257 --> 00:39:04,635
My great thanks, Master Ford.

579
00:39:04,800 --> 00:39:06,894
No, my thanks to you.

580
00:39:07,052 --> 00:39:09,351
And it is the least of it.

581
00:39:09,514 --> 00:39:12,768
I hope it brings us both
much joy over the years.

582
00:39:32,996 --> 00:39:34,248
(STRUMMING)

583
00:39:39,293 --> 00:39:40,637
(SOBBING)

584
00:39:43,463 --> 00:39:44,635
God!

585
00:39:49,219 --> 00:39:50,641
Eliza.

586
00:39:55,726 --> 00:39:56,978
Eliza.

587
00:39:57,728 --> 00:39:58,730
Stop!

588
00:39:59,271 --> 00:40:01,148
Stop your wailing!

589
00:40:03,610 --> 00:40:05,032
If you let yourself be overcome

590
00:40:05,152 --> 00:40:06,621
by sorrow, you will drown in it.

591
00:40:06,778 --> 00:40:08,496
Have you stopped crying
for your children?

592
00:40:10,324 --> 00:40:13,829
You make no sounds, but will you
ever let them go in your heart?

593
00:40:18,248 --> 00:40:20,001
They are as my flesh.

594
00:40:20,168 --> 00:40:22,170
Then who is distressed?

595
00:40:22,920 --> 00:40:25,173
Do I upset the master
and the mistress?

596
00:40:25,340 --> 00:40:27,684
Do you care less about my loss
than their well-being?

597
00:40:27,842 --> 00:40:29,184
Master Ford is a decent man.

598
00:40:29,344 --> 00:40:30,469
He is a slaver!

599
00:40:30,637 --> 00:40:31,653
Under the circumstances.

600
00:40:31,679 --> 00:40:33,476
Under the circumstances,
he is a slaver.

601
00:40:33,806 --> 00:40:35,682
But you truckle at his boot.

602
00:40:35,849 --> 00:40:37,476
You luxuriate in his favor.

603
00:40:37,643 --> 00:40:39,362
I survive!

604
00:40:39,519 --> 00:40:41,568
I will not fall into despair!

605
00:40:41,731 --> 00:40:43,699
I will offer up my talents
to Master Ford!

606
00:40:43,858 --> 00:40:46,657
I will keep myself hearty
until freedom is opportune!

607
00:40:46,818 --> 00:40:48,867
Ford is your opportunity?

608
00:40:49,530 --> 00:40:52,409
You think he does not know that
you are more than you suggest?

609
00:40:52,574 --> 00:40:54,248
But he does nothing for you.

610
00:40:54,409 --> 00:40:55,581
Nothing.

611
00:40:56,204 --> 00:40:59,503
You are no better
than prized livestock.

612
00:41:00,041 --> 00:41:01,418
Call for him. Call!

613
00:41:01,583 --> 00:41:03,711
Tell him of your
previous circumstances,

614
00:41:03,878 --> 00:41:06,050
and see what it
earns you, Solomon.

615
00:41:07,547 --> 00:41:10,391
So, you've settled into
your role as Platt, then?

616
00:41:11,302 --> 00:41:12,362
(DISHES CLATTERING)

617
00:41:12,387 --> 00:41:15,614
My back is thick with scars...

618
00:41:15,639 --> 00:41:18,063
for protesting my freedom.

619
00:41:18,226 --> 00:41:19,648
Do not accuse me.

620
00:41:20,478 --> 00:41:24,072
I accuse you of nothing.
I cannot accuse.

621
00:41:24,231 --> 00:41:27,155
I have done dishonorable
things to survive...

622
00:41:27,318 --> 00:41:30,322
and for all of them,
I have ended up here.

623
00:41:30,822 --> 00:41:33,871
No better than
if I stood up for myself.

624
00:41:34,492 --> 00:41:36,744
God, forgive me.

625
00:41:36,911 --> 00:41:39,710
Solomon, let me weep
for my children!

626
00:41:41,456 --> 00:41:42,925
(SOBBING)

627
00:41:50,090 --> 00:41:52,184
FORD: <i>"Whosoever,
therefore, shall humble"</i>

628
00:41:52,300 --> 00:41:54,429
<i>"himself as
this little child..."</i>

629
00:41:54,929 --> 00:41:58,775
"the same is the greatest in the
kingdom of heaven." (ELIZA WAILING)

630
00:41:58,932 --> 00:42:03,860
"And who so shall receive one
such little child in my name..."

631
00:42:04,021 --> 00:42:05,864
I cannot have that
kind of depression about.

632
00:42:06,023 --> 00:42:08,197
"But who so shall offend
one of these little ones..."

633
00:42:08,358 --> 00:42:11,253
"it were better for him that a millstone
were hanged about his neck..."

634
00:42:11,278 --> 00:42:12,505
(SOBBING)

635
00:42:12,530 --> 00:42:16,125
"and he were drowned
in the depth of the sea."

636
00:42:17,201 --> 00:42:18,202
Amen.

637
00:42:18,744 --> 00:42:19,916
ALL: Amen.

638
00:42:32,717 --> 00:42:34,811
Make them boards flush.

639
00:42:35,219 --> 00:42:36,141
They are, sir.

640
00:42:36,304 --> 00:42:38,306
No, they is no such thing.

641
00:42:39,806 --> 00:42:43,061
They are as smooth to the
touch as a yearling's coat.

642
00:42:45,646 --> 00:42:47,568
Are you calling me a liar, boy?

643
00:42:50,485 --> 00:42:52,829
It's all a matter
of perspective, sir.

644
00:42:53,329 --> 00:42:55,130
From where you stand,
you may see differently,

645
00:42:55,155 --> 00:42:56,782
but the hands are not mistaken.

646
00:42:57,324 --> 00:43:01,579
I simply ask that you use all your
senses before rendering judgment.

647
00:43:03,121 --> 00:43:06,342
Oh, my, you are a brute.

648
00:43:07,835 --> 00:43:09,427
You are a dog.
(SHOUTS)

649
00:43:10,088 --> 00:43:12,762
And no better for
following instruction!

650
00:43:14,132 --> 00:43:15,193
I do as ordered.

651
00:43:15,217 --> 00:43:16,418
Then you'll be up at daybreak.

652
00:43:16,677 --> 00:43:19,351
You will procure
a keg of nails from Chapin...

653
00:43:19,514 --> 00:43:21,516
and commence to
putting on clapboards.

654
00:43:21,681 --> 00:43:22,853
Yes, sir.

655
00:43:28,313 --> 00:43:29,987
Make them boards flush.

656
00:43:38,865 --> 00:43:41,369
ELIZA: No, please!
Please, Sam!

657
00:43:41,536 --> 00:43:43,880
Where am I going?
Where am I going, Sam?

658
00:43:44,371 --> 00:43:46,875
Solomon! Solomon!

659
00:43:47,291 --> 00:43:48,713
Solomon!

660
00:43:49,668 --> 00:43:51,342
Solomon!

661
00:43:51,753 --> 00:43:53,175
(SOBBING)

662
00:43:55,007 --> 00:43:57,054
Solomon!

663
00:44:02,472 --> 00:44:05,818
ELIZA: <i>When I say I had my
Master's favor, you understand.</i>

664
00:44:08,396 --> 00:44:09,521
And for nine years...

665
00:44:09,688 --> 00:44:13,568
he blessed me with every
comfort and luxury in life.

666
00:44:13,733 --> 00:44:16,202
Silks and jewels...

667
00:44:16,362 --> 00:44:18,831
and even servants
to wait upon us.

668
00:44:20,907 --> 00:44:23,331
Such was our life.

669
00:44:23,494 --> 00:44:26,373
And the life of this beautiful
girl I bore for him.

670
00:44:29,541 --> 00:44:31,715
But Master Berry's daughter...

671
00:44:32,670 --> 00:44:35,548
she always looked at me
with an unkind nature.

672
00:44:36,215 --> 00:44:40,061
And she hated Emily, no matter she
and Emily were flesh of flesh.

673
00:44:43,222 --> 00:44:44,849
As Master Berry's health failed,

674
00:44:44,974 --> 00:44:46,601
she gained power
of the household...

675
00:44:47,023 --> 00:44:49,744
and eventually, I was brought to the
city under the false pretense...

676
00:44:49,769 --> 00:44:52,568
of our free papers
being executed.

677
00:44:56,610 --> 00:44:58,909
My poor children.

678
00:45:21,052 --> 00:45:22,519
(BELL TOLLING)

679
00:45:27,266 --> 00:45:28,643
(HAMMERING)

680
00:45:37,735 --> 00:45:40,614
I thought I told you to commence
to putting on clapboards.

681
00:45:41,655 --> 00:45:44,500
Yes, Master, I'm about it.
These have all been replaced.

682
00:45:45,659 --> 00:45:47,913
And didn't I tell you
to get a keg of nails?

683
00:45:48,079 --> 00:45:49,751
And so, I did.

684
00:45:50,581 --> 00:45:51,923
So, you did.

685
00:45:53,000 --> 00:45:55,673
God damn you. I thought
you knowed something!

686
00:45:55,835 --> 00:45:57,338
I did as instructed.

687
00:45:57,505 --> 00:46:00,724
If there's something wrong, it's
wrong with the instruction.

688
00:46:01,175 --> 00:46:03,177
You black bastard.

689
00:46:03,719 --> 00:46:08,599
You goddamn black bastard.

690
00:46:08,766 --> 00:46:10,813
Strip your clothes.

691
00:46:13,144 --> 00:46:14,317
Strip.

692
00:46:15,313 --> 00:46:16,860
I will not.

693
00:46:21,112 --> 00:46:22,364
(BOTH GRUNTING)

694
00:46:24,739 --> 00:46:25,831
(TIBEATS GROANS)

695
00:46:26,409 --> 00:46:32,541
You will not live
to see another day, nigger!

696
00:46:33,581 --> 00:46:34,673
Help!

697
00:46:34,875 --> 00:46:36,376
(SCREAMING)

698
00:46:40,463 --> 00:46:41,715
Murder!

699
00:46:44,010 --> 00:46:45,010
I'm sorry!

700
00:46:45,635 --> 00:46:47,889
I'm sorry!
I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

701
00:46:48,972 --> 00:46:50,646
(WHIMPERING)

702
00:46:50,932 --> 00:46:52,525
CHAPIN: What is the matter?

703
00:46:52,893 --> 00:46:54,190
What is the matter?

704
00:46:55,061 --> 00:46:56,438
Master Tibeats wants to whip me

705
00:46:56,563 --> 00:46:58,039
for using the nails you gave me.

706
00:46:58,065 --> 00:46:59,112
(SPITS)

707
00:46:59,858 --> 00:47:01,987
This ain't done by half.

708
00:47:02,445 --> 00:47:04,664
I will have flesh.

709
00:47:04,822 --> 00:47:07,074
And I will have all of it!

710
00:47:07,282 --> 00:47:08,909
(PANTING)

711
00:47:10,744 --> 00:47:11,836
CHAPIN: Do not stir.

712
00:47:12,329 --> 00:47:15,708
Do not leave the plantation. For,
if you run, I cannot protect you.

713
00:47:16,458 --> 00:47:17,755
Stay here.

714
00:47:18,585 --> 00:47:19,929
(PANTING)

715
00:47:55,206 --> 00:47:57,083
(HORSES APPROACHING)

716
00:48:08,427 --> 00:48:09,643
(GROANING)

717
00:48:11,179 --> 00:48:12,806
(CHOKING)

718
00:48:21,148 --> 00:48:25,072
Gentlemen, whoever moves
that nigger is a dead man.

719
00:48:25,568 --> 00:48:26,920
(GASPING)

720
00:48:26,945 --> 00:48:29,869
I am the overseer
on this plantation.

721
00:48:30,032 --> 00:48:32,751
William Ford holds
the mortgage on Platt.

722
00:48:33,119 --> 00:48:35,668
If you hang him,
he will lose his debt.

723
00:48:36,079 --> 00:48:38,503
You have no claim to his life.

724
00:48:38,958 --> 00:48:40,505
As for you two...

725
00:48:40,668 --> 00:48:43,672
if you have any regard
for your own safety...

726
00:48:43,838 --> 00:48:44,804
I say, be gone!

727
00:48:48,384 --> 00:48:50,226
You got no cause!

728
00:48:50,385 --> 00:48:53,856
Platt is mine, and mine
to do with as I please!

729
00:48:54,014 --> 00:48:55,936
If you touch...
(COCKS GUN)

730
00:49:09,530 --> 00:49:10,952
(PANTING)

731
00:49:22,293 --> 00:49:22,963
Sam!

732
00:49:23,793 --> 00:49:26,092
Fetch the mule.
Get Master Ford.

733
00:49:29,048 --> 00:49:31,016
(CONTINUES PANTING)

734
00:51:10,275 --> 00:51:11,447
(COUGHS)

735
00:51:37,385 --> 00:51:38,603
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)

736
00:51:45,101 --> 00:51:47,195
(GASPING)

737
00:52:14,005 --> 00:52:15,382
(HORSE APPROACHING)

738
00:52:21,012 --> 00:52:23,266
Platt. Poor Platt.

739
00:52:25,643 --> 00:52:26,518
(GRUNTS)

740
00:52:31,398 --> 00:52:32,523
(DOOR CLOSES)

741
00:52:41,574 --> 00:52:42,827
(DOOR OPENS)

742
00:52:52,878 --> 00:52:55,347
I believe Tibeats is skulking
about the premises somewhere.

743
00:52:55,505 --> 00:52:58,726
He wants you dead,
and he will have it so.

744
00:52:58,884 --> 00:53:01,103
It's no longer
safe for you here.

745
00:53:01,260 --> 00:53:05,061
And I don't believe you will
remain passive if Tibeats attacks.

746
00:53:05,224 --> 00:53:08,273
I have transferred
my debt to Edwin Epps.

747
00:53:08,434 --> 00:53:10,358
He will take charge...
(HORSE NEIGHING)

748
00:53:31,041 --> 00:53:32,713
Master Ford.

749
00:53:35,086 --> 00:53:37,840
You must know
that I'm not a slave.

750
00:53:38,297 --> 00:53:39,344
I cannot hear that.

751
00:53:39,507 --> 00:53:41,476
Before I came to you,
I was a freeman.

752
00:53:41,635 --> 00:53:44,309
I'm trying to save your life!

753
00:53:45,472 --> 00:53:48,021
And I have a debt
to be mindful of.

754
00:53:50,393 --> 00:53:52,442
And that is to Edwin Epps now.

755
00:53:52,603 --> 00:53:55,402
And he is a hard man. Prides
himself on being a nigger breaker.

756
00:53:55,565 --> 00:53:58,614
But truthfully, I could find
no others who would take you.

757
00:53:59,193 --> 00:54:01,697
You've made
a reputation of yourself.

758
00:54:02,364 --> 00:54:07,164
Whatever the circumstances, you
are an exceptional nigger, Platt.

759
00:54:09,079 --> 00:54:11,878
But I fear no good
will come of it.

760
00:54:34,605 --> 00:54:36,402
"And that servant..."

761
00:54:37,565 --> 00:54:40,114
"which knew
his lord's will..."

762
00:54:41,527 --> 00:54:44,952
Which knew his lord's will.

763
00:54:49,036 --> 00:54:51,710
"...and prepared
not himself..."

764
00:54:53,373 --> 00:54:55,876
Prepared not himself.

765
00:54:59,922 --> 00:55:02,596
"...neither did
according to his will..."

766
00:55:04,550 --> 00:55:07,724
"shall be beaten
with many stripes."

767
00:55:09,056 --> 00:55:10,523
Do you hear that?

768
00:55:11,182 --> 00:55:12,525
"Stripes."

769
00:55:13,768 --> 00:55:15,896
That nigger that
don't obey his lord...

770
00:55:16,063 --> 00:55:18,110
That's his master, do you see?

771
00:55:18,940 --> 00:55:23,617
That there nigger shall be
beaten with many stripes.

772
00:55:25,239 --> 00:55:29,039
Now, "many"
signifies a great many.

773
00:55:29,576 --> 00:55:33,422
40, 100, 150 lashes.

774
00:55:38,085 --> 00:55:39,677
That's scripture.

775
00:55:40,420 --> 00:55:42,092
(WOMAN HUMMING)

776
00:55:42,965 --> 00:55:44,637
(ALL HUMMING)

777
00:55:56,061 --> 00:55:57,608
EDWARD: Pick that cotton.

778
00:55:57,771 --> 00:55:59,693
Move along, now.
(WHIP CRACKS)

779
00:56:01,942 --> 00:56:04,786
TREACH: Come on, Edward!
Drive them niggers!

780
00:56:04,945 --> 00:56:07,949
Pick that cotton!
Move along, now.

781
00:56:08,657 --> 00:56:10,625
TREACH: What are you
doing, boy? Come on!

782
00:56:13,452 --> 00:56:15,672
TREACH: 240 for Bob.

783
00:56:16,123 --> 00:56:18,090
EPPS: What
you got for James?

784
00:56:18,500 --> 00:56:20,628
295 pounds.

785
00:56:20,793 --> 00:56:23,842
That's real good, boy.
That's real good.

786
00:56:24,463 --> 00:56:26,592
182 for Platt.

787
00:56:28,217 --> 00:56:31,097
How much can even an
average nigger pick a day?

788
00:56:31,262 --> 00:56:32,514
200 pounds.

789
00:56:32,681 --> 00:56:34,557
This nigger ain't even average.

790
00:56:36,351 --> 00:56:38,648
512 pounds for Patsey.

791
00:56:38,811 --> 00:56:41,485
512!

792
00:56:42,398 --> 00:56:46,403
You menfolk got no shame
letting Patsey out-pick you.

793
00:56:47,987 --> 00:56:51,538
The day ain't yet come she
swung lower than 500 pounds.

794
00:56:54,869 --> 00:56:57,338
Queen of the fields, she is.

795
00:56:57,496 --> 00:56:58,543
TREACH: 138 pounds...

796
00:56:58,706 --> 00:57:00,458
I ain't done, Treach.

797
00:57:01,168 --> 00:57:04,762
Ain't I owed a minute to luxuriate
on the work Patsey done?

798
00:57:05,297 --> 00:57:06,469
Yes, sir.

799
00:57:10,594 --> 00:57:12,186
Damn queen.

800
00:57:13,679 --> 00:57:16,684
Born and bred to the field.

801
00:57:18,226 --> 00:57:20,603
A nigger among niggers.

802
00:57:22,688 --> 00:57:24,690
And God gave her to me.

803
00:57:28,862 --> 00:57:31,786
A lesson in the rewards
of righteous living.

804
00:57:33,742 --> 00:57:35,960
All be observant to that.

805
00:57:37,079 --> 00:57:39,047
All!

806
00:57:39,873 --> 00:57:42,376
Now, Treach. Now speak.

807
00:57:43,085 --> 00:57:46,088
138 pounds for Phebe.

808
00:57:46,797 --> 00:57:49,891
Hit 145 yesterday.
Pull her out.

809
00:57:50,717 --> 00:57:52,719
206 pounds for George.

810
00:57:53,135 --> 00:57:55,059
How much he pick yesterday?

811
00:57:56,097 --> 00:57:57,565
229.

812
00:57:57,724 --> 00:57:58,896
Get him out.

813
00:57:59,059 --> 00:58:00,481
Come on, get.

814
00:58:02,396 --> 00:58:03,818
Come on.

815
00:58:03,981 --> 00:58:05,778
EPPS: Come on, boy, move!

816
00:58:11,405 --> 00:58:12,755
(WHIP CRACKING)

817
00:58:12,780 --> 00:58:14,077
(MAN GROANING)
(WOMAN GROANING)

818
00:58:26,670 --> 00:58:28,047
(HUMMING)

819
00:59:46,958 --> 00:59:48,300
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

820
00:59:48,751 --> 00:59:50,048
(DOOR OPENS)

821
00:59:50,336 --> 00:59:52,054
(SINGING)

822
00:59:54,048 --> 00:59:55,016
Get up!

823
00:59:55,175 --> 00:59:56,643
We dance tonight!
Get up!

824
00:59:56,802 --> 00:59:58,304
Get your fiddle, Platt.
Get up!

825
00:59:58,469 --> 01:00:00,518
Come on!
Get, get, get!

826
01:00:00,679 --> 01:00:02,523
Come on, Platt. Come on!

827
01:00:02,849 --> 01:00:04,284
(UPBEAT FIDDLE MUSIC PLAYING)

828
01:00:04,309 --> 01:00:05,561
(EPPS CLAPPING)

829
01:00:14,318 --> 01:00:17,322
Come on, where's your merriment?
Move your feet!

830
01:00:29,166 --> 01:00:30,965
(GROANS)
(MUSIC STOPS)

831
01:00:31,293 --> 01:00:32,420
MISTRESS EPPS: Sell her.
(PATSEY SOBBING)

832
01:00:32,586 --> 01:00:33,588
EPPS: What's all this?

833
01:00:33,755 --> 01:00:36,257
You will sell the negress.

834
01:00:36,423 --> 01:00:38,222
Sell little Pats?

835
01:00:38,385 --> 01:00:41,103
She pick with more vigor
than any other nigger.

836
01:00:41,554 --> 01:00:42,405
Choose another to go.

837
01:00:42,429 --> 01:00:44,056
No other.

838
01:00:44,224 --> 01:00:45,567
Sell her.

839
01:00:45,934 --> 01:00:47,311
I will not.

840
01:00:48,561 --> 01:00:51,532
You will remove that black
bitch from this property...

841
01:00:51,690 --> 01:00:54,614
or I'll take myself
back to Cheneyville.

842
01:00:55,610 --> 01:00:57,077
(SOBBING CONTINUES)

843
01:00:58,362 --> 01:01:00,661
Back to that hog's trough
where I found you?

844
01:01:03,617 --> 01:01:07,498
Do not set yourself up
against Patsey, my dear.

845
01:01:11,458 --> 01:01:13,257
Because I will rid myself of you

846
01:01:13,420 --> 01:01:15,262
well before I do away with her.

847
01:01:23,679 --> 01:01:24,726
What you looking at?

848
01:01:26,016 --> 01:01:27,688
Damn woman.

849
01:01:28,476 --> 01:01:30,570
I won't have my mood spoiled.

850
01:01:30,978 --> 01:01:32,822
I will not.

851
01:01:34,190 --> 01:01:35,030
Dance.
(MUSIC RESUMES)

852
01:01:35,275 --> 01:01:36,902
Dance, I says!
(GROANING)

853
01:01:41,447 --> 01:01:42,949
Come on!

854
01:01:43,115 --> 01:01:46,510
Pick it up, Platt.
Play that fiddle, boy.

855
01:01:46,536 --> 01:01:47,536
(EPPS WHOOPING)

856
01:01:56,295 --> 01:01:57,717
(BLOWING)

857
01:02:22,989 --> 01:02:24,114
MISTRESS EPPS: Platt.

858
01:02:25,992 --> 01:02:27,460
Yes, Mistress?

859
01:02:29,496 --> 01:02:32,045
Can you find your
way to Bartholomew's?

860
01:02:32,666 --> 01:02:33,918
I can, ma'am.

861
01:02:34,333 --> 01:02:36,085
This is a list of
goods and sundries.

862
01:02:36,253 --> 01:02:39,177
You will take it to be filled
and return immediately.

863
01:02:39,338 --> 01:02:41,557
Take your tag.

864
01:02:41,715 --> 01:02:43,514
Tell Bartholomew to
add it to our debt.

865
01:02:43,677 --> 01:02:44,677
Yes, Mistress.

866
01:02:46,846 --> 01:02:48,940
Where you from, Platt?

867
01:02:51,059 --> 01:02:52,311
I told you.

868
01:02:52,476 --> 01:02:54,228
Tell me again.

869
01:02:54,771 --> 01:02:55,771
Washington.

870
01:02:55,938 --> 01:02:56,905
Who were your master?

871
01:02:57,023 --> 01:02:57,989
Master name a Freeman.

872
01:02:58,148 --> 01:02:59,900
Was he a learned man?

873
01:03:00,735 --> 01:03:02,327
I suppose so.

874
01:03:02,487 --> 01:03:03,909
He learn you to read?

875
01:03:05,864 --> 01:03:07,992
A word, here or there.

876
01:03:08,335 --> 01:03:10,094
But I have no understanding
of the written...

877
01:03:10,119 --> 01:03:12,338
Don't trouble yourself with it.

878
01:03:12,789 --> 01:03:16,293
Same as the rest. Master brought
you here to work, that's all.

879
01:03:17,460 --> 01:03:20,134
Any more will
earn you 100 lashes.

880
01:04:07,885 --> 01:04:09,478
(PANTING)

881
01:04:18,813 --> 01:04:20,280
(DOG WHIMPERING)

882
01:04:26,112 --> 01:04:27,112
Come here, boy.

883
01:04:30,115 --> 01:04:31,458
Come on.

884
01:04:47,634 --> 01:04:49,306
Where you going, boy?

885
01:04:49,469 --> 01:04:51,972
On my way to Bartholomew's.

886
01:04:52,137 --> 01:04:54,391
Sent by Mistress Epps.

887
01:04:58,186 --> 01:05:00,153
You best get there, then.

888
01:05:01,231 --> 01:05:02,824
Get there quick.

889
01:05:15,994 --> 01:05:17,429
(MEN CHOKING)

890
01:05:17,454 --> 01:05:18,831
(DOG BARKING)

891
01:05:31,677 --> 01:05:33,351
(SHOPKEEPER MUTTERING)

892
01:05:51,864 --> 01:05:53,208
Any trouble?

893
01:05:53,365 --> 01:05:55,869
No, ma'am. No trouble.

894
01:06:43,750 --> 01:06:45,251
(PANTING)

895
01:06:54,594 --> 01:06:56,311
Platt Epps, good Sunday morning.

896
01:06:56,471 --> 01:06:57,768
Good morning, Master Shaw.

897
01:06:57,931 --> 01:07:00,400
Master sent me to retrieve Patsey.
May I approach?

898
01:07:00,557 --> 01:07:01,775
You may.

899
01:07:03,101 --> 01:07:04,695
(PANTING)

900
01:07:06,105 --> 01:07:07,231
(WOMEN LAUGHING)

901
01:07:12,237 --> 01:07:13,864
Excuse me, Mistress Shaw.

902
01:07:14,280 --> 01:07:15,623
Nigger Platt.

903
01:07:15,782 --> 01:07:17,579
Patsey, Master
wishes you to return.

904
01:07:17,742 --> 01:07:19,369
The Sabbath day,
I is free to roam.

905
01:07:19,786 --> 01:07:22,539
Master sent me running to fetch
you, said no time should be wasted.

906
01:07:22,789 --> 01:07:24,416
Drink of tea?

907
01:07:24,581 --> 01:07:26,458
Thank you, Mistress,
but I don't dare.

908
01:07:26,626 --> 01:07:28,628
Would you know of
Master Epps's consternation...

909
01:07:28,795 --> 01:07:31,969
to be any lessened
with your timely return?

910
01:07:32,632 --> 01:07:34,929
Anger's his constant condition.

911
01:07:35,092 --> 01:07:35,889
Sit.

912
01:07:36,594 --> 01:07:38,641
Sit and drink
the tea that I offered.

913
01:07:43,768 --> 01:07:45,954
What'n be Epps's concern?

914
01:07:45,978 --> 01:07:47,275
(SIGHS)

915
01:07:47,771 --> 01:07:49,489
I'd rather not say.

916
01:07:50,065 --> 01:07:54,320
Oh, little gossip on the Sabbath be fine.
All things in moderation.

917
01:07:56,072 --> 01:07:58,119
As you are aware...

918
01:07:58,282 --> 01:08:04,164
Master Epps is a man
of hard countenance.

919
01:08:04,496 --> 01:08:06,670
You know he has ill feeling
towards your husband.

920
01:08:06,833 --> 01:08:08,085
He do.

921
01:08:09,001 --> 01:08:11,096
Master Epps has somehow
come to believe...

922
01:08:11,253 --> 01:08:15,259
that Master Shaw
is something of a lothario.

923
01:08:16,842 --> 01:08:19,311
A misguided belief, no doubt.

924
01:08:19,470 --> 01:08:20,641
No doubt...

925
01:08:20,805 --> 01:08:22,932
if not born out of truth itself.

926
01:08:25,184 --> 01:08:26,777
I meant no disrespect.

927
01:08:27,185 --> 01:08:28,984
He ain't heard you.

928
01:08:29,354 --> 01:08:31,666
SOLOMON: I meant no
disrespect to you, Mistress.

929
01:08:31,690 --> 01:08:33,113
(LAUGHS)

930
01:08:34,569 --> 01:08:38,163
Got no cause to worry
for my sensibilities.

931
01:08:38,905 --> 01:08:43,502
I ain't felt the end of a lash
in more years I can recall.

932
01:08:43,661 --> 01:08:45,755
I ain't worked a field, neither.

933
01:08:46,372 --> 01:08:48,170
Where once I served...

934
01:08:48,332 --> 01:08:51,256
now, I have others serving me.

935
01:08:51,877 --> 01:08:54,471
The cost to
my current existence...

936
01:08:54,631 --> 01:08:57,760
be Master Shaw
broadcasting his affections...

937
01:08:57,925 --> 01:09:00,769
and me enjoying
the pantomime of his fidelity.

938
01:09:02,137 --> 01:09:06,564
If that what keep me from cotton
picking niggers, that what it be.

939
01:09:06,725 --> 01:09:10,447
A small and reasonable price
to be paid, for sure.

940
01:09:14,900 --> 01:09:17,449
I know what it like
to be the object

941
01:09:17,569 --> 01:09:20,163
of Master's predilections
and peculiarities.

942
01:09:21,323 --> 01:09:23,952
A lusty visit in the night...

943
01:09:24,118 --> 01:09:26,587
or a visitation with the whip.

944
01:09:27,954 --> 01:09:29,502
Take comfort, Patsey.

945
01:09:29,748 --> 01:09:31,877
The good Lord will manage Epps.

946
01:09:32,335 --> 01:09:36,886
In His own time, the good
Lord will manage them all.

947
01:09:37,172 --> 01:09:40,426
The curse of the pharaohs
were a poor example...

948
01:09:40,592 --> 01:09:43,516
of what wait for
the plantation class.

949
01:09:48,935 --> 01:09:50,608
This is nice.

950
01:10:01,948 --> 01:10:04,497
EPPS: Pats. Patsey!

951
01:10:04,658 --> 01:10:06,332
Do not look in his direction.
Continue on.

952
01:10:06,953 --> 01:10:08,704
Patsey!
Found her, Master.

953
01:10:09,204 --> 01:10:11,502
And brought her back,
just as instructed.

954
01:10:14,085 --> 01:10:16,212
What did you just now tell her?

955
01:10:16,378 --> 01:10:18,051
What did you say to Pats?

956
01:10:19,215 --> 01:10:20,966
No words were spoken,
none of consequence.

957
01:10:22,760 --> 01:10:24,353
You're a liar.

958
01:10:24,679 --> 01:10:26,646
You damn liar.

959
01:10:27,390 --> 01:10:29,688
I saw you talking with her.

960
01:10:30,643 --> 01:10:32,189
Tell me.

961
01:10:33,813 --> 01:10:35,530
I cannot speak of
what did not occur.

962
01:10:35,814 --> 01:10:37,567
I'll cut your black throat!

963
01:10:37,734 --> 01:10:38,859
Master!

964
01:10:39,402 --> 01:10:40,823
You come here.

965
01:10:41,194 --> 01:10:42,354
Master Epps.
I said come here!

966
01:10:42,488 --> 01:10:43,887
I brought her back,
just like you...

967
01:10:45,240 --> 01:10:46,708
Come here!
Master!

968
01:10:48,911 --> 01:10:49,912
Master.

969
01:10:52,582 --> 01:10:54,835
I got her, just as instructed.

970
01:10:56,210 --> 01:10:57,211
Master Epps!

971
01:10:57,502 --> 01:10:59,005
You stay away from Pats, boy.

972
01:11:00,840 --> 01:11:02,307
(PIGS SQUEALING)

973
01:11:05,219 --> 01:11:06,561
Master Epps.

974
01:11:08,180 --> 01:11:09,273
(GROANS)

975
01:11:19,692 --> 01:11:21,113
(LAUGHING)

976
01:11:22,653 --> 01:11:23,824
(PANTING)

977
01:11:27,115 --> 01:11:28,412
(CONTINUES LAUGHING)

978
01:11:33,372 --> 01:11:35,248
It's the Lord's day.

979
01:11:36,708 --> 01:11:39,587
Ain't nothing Christian
in us carrying on like this.

980
01:11:40,046 --> 01:11:41,592
(PANTING)

981
01:11:46,551 --> 01:11:48,020
I concede to you.

982
01:11:50,722 --> 01:11:52,020
In the name of valor...

983
01:11:53,684 --> 01:11:54,900
help your master to his feet.

984
01:11:59,564 --> 01:12:00,690
I'm gonna kill you!

985
01:12:01,192 --> 01:12:02,694
MISTRESS EPPS: What's the fuss?

986
01:12:02,859 --> 01:12:04,533
Master Epps
believed Patsey and me

987
01:12:04,654 --> 01:12:06,327
to be in conversation
when we were not.

988
01:12:06,488 --> 01:12:07,740
I tried to explain,
but it's led to all this.

989
01:12:07,907 --> 01:12:08,748
What is it?

990
01:12:09,199 --> 01:12:12,043
You can't remain the Sabbath
without her under your eye?

991
01:12:12,203 --> 01:12:14,012
You are
a no-account bastard.

992
01:12:14,037 --> 01:12:16,039
A filthy, godless heathen.

993
01:12:16,207 --> 01:12:18,835
My bed is too holy
for you to share.

994
01:12:19,001 --> 01:12:20,092
What's he been telling you?

995
01:12:20,252 --> 01:12:21,595
Of your misbegotten ways.

996
01:12:21,753 --> 01:12:23,756
And he would know
what of anything?

997
01:12:24,881 --> 01:12:26,759
I ain't even
spoken with him today.

998
01:12:27,551 --> 01:12:29,429
You lying nigger, Platt.

999
01:12:30,095 --> 01:12:31,188
Have I?

1000
01:12:33,557 --> 01:12:34,774
Have I?

1001
01:12:37,353 --> 01:12:39,775
There. There's
all the truth he got.

1002
01:12:40,773 --> 01:12:42,024
Damn nigger.

1003
01:13:59,100 --> 01:14:00,193
(GRUNTS)

1004
01:14:08,194 --> 01:14:09,570
(PANTING)

1005
01:14:16,202 --> 01:14:17,373
(GRUNTS)

1006
01:14:21,498 --> 01:14:22,966
(PANTING)

1007
01:14:33,886 --> 01:14:35,137
Patsey.

1008
01:14:41,060 --> 01:14:42,403
(CHOKING)

1009
01:14:53,572 --> 01:14:55,573
(GASPING)

1010
01:16:03,893 --> 01:16:05,485
(UPBEAT FIDDLE MUSIC PLAYING)

1011
01:16:31,921 --> 01:16:34,344
MISTRESS EPPS: A moment
from the dancing.

1012
01:16:35,507 --> 01:16:37,761
Come sample what
I baked for y'all.

1013
01:16:37,926 --> 01:16:40,738
MEN: Thank you, Mistress.

1014
01:16:40,762 --> 01:16:41,863
WOMEN: Thank you, Mistress.

1015
01:16:41,889 --> 01:16:44,016
There will be
none for you, Patsey.

1016
01:16:45,518 --> 01:16:47,020
You see that?

1017
01:16:47,394 --> 01:16:50,193
You see that look
of insolence she give me?

1018
01:16:51,023 --> 01:16:52,524
I seen nothing
but her turn away.

1019
01:16:52,690 --> 01:16:54,909
Are you blind or ignorant?

1020
01:16:55,069 --> 01:16:57,367
It was hot, hateful scorn.

1021
01:16:57,529 --> 01:16:59,623
It filled that black face.

1022
01:17:00,198 --> 01:17:01,509
You tell me you didn't see it...

1023
01:17:01,533 --> 01:17:05,538
it's because you choose not to
look, or are you saying I lie?

1024
01:17:05,703 --> 01:17:08,047
Whatever it was, it passed.

1025
01:17:08,707 --> 01:17:11,460
Is that how you
are with the niggers?

1026
01:17:12,043 --> 01:17:15,217
Letting every ill thought
fester inside them?

1027
01:17:15,965 --> 01:17:17,386
Look at them.

1028
01:17:17,550 --> 01:17:19,722
They foul with it.

1029
01:17:19,885 --> 01:17:21,979
They foul with their hate.

1030
01:17:22,720 --> 01:17:26,725
You let it be, it's gonna come
back to us in the dark of night.

1031
01:17:26,891 --> 01:17:28,439
You want that?

1032
01:17:29,145 --> 01:17:31,863
You want them
black animals leave us

1033
01:17:31,980 --> 01:17:34,654
gut like pigs in our own sleep?

1034
01:17:35,067 --> 01:17:36,193
Oh...

1035
01:17:36,819 --> 01:17:40,073
You are manless.

1036
01:17:40,238 --> 01:17:42,912
A damn eunuch if there ever was.

1037
01:17:43,492 --> 01:17:45,335
If you won't stand
for me, I pray you'd

1038
