BASS: Right to the end.

1317
01:42:12,627 --> 01:42:14,173
Hey, Bass.

1318
01:42:15,087 --> 01:42:16,555
Oh, no, no, no.

1319
01:42:16,713 --> 01:42:19,182
EPPS: No shame in taking
respite from the heat.

1320
01:42:19,341 --> 01:42:21,060
Drink, shade.

1321
01:42:21,217 --> 01:42:23,863
It's ungodly for travelers,
hearty or otherwise.

1322
01:42:23,887 --> 01:42:25,265
(LAUGHING)

1323
01:42:28,893 --> 01:42:29,984
What's funny?

1324
01:42:30,144 --> 01:42:33,864
Epps, I merely mean to finish
the work at hand, as requested.

1325
01:42:34,023 --> 01:42:35,820
And as paid for.

1326
01:42:35,983 --> 01:42:37,780
If something rubs you wrongly...

1327
01:42:37,943 --> 01:42:40,867
I offer you the opportunity
to speak on it.

1328
01:42:44,115 --> 01:42:46,743
You ask plainly, so I
will tell you plainly.

1329
01:42:47,536 --> 01:42:51,756
What amused me just then was your concern
for my well-being in this heat...

1330
01:42:51,998 --> 01:42:54,969
when, quite frankly, the
condition of your laborers...

1331
01:42:55,127 --> 01:42:56,395
"The condition of my laborers"?

1332
01:42:56,420 --> 01:42:58,421
BASS: It is horrid.
It's all wrong.

1333
01:42:58,588 --> 01:42:59,841
All wrong, Mr. Epps.

1334
01:43:00,006 --> 01:43:02,260
They ain't hired help.

1335
01:43:02,426 --> 01:43:03,472
They're my property.

1336
01:43:04,302 --> 01:43:05,304
You say that with pride.

1337
01:43:05,470 --> 01:43:07,144
I say it as fact.

1338
01:43:09,225 --> 01:43:11,899
If this conversation
concerns what is factual

1339
01:43:12,019 --> 01:43:14,693
and what is not,
then it must be said...

1340
01:43:14,854 --> 01:43:17,984
that there is no justice nor
righteousness in their slavery.

1341
01:43:18,818 --> 01:43:20,945
But you do open up
an interesting question.

1342
01:43:22,113 --> 01:43:23,534
What right have
you to your niggers,

1343
01:43:23,655 --> 01:43:25,033
when you come down to the point?

1344
01:43:25,448 --> 01:43:26,746
What right?
Mmm.

1345
01:43:27,368 --> 01:43:30,212
I bought them.
I paid for them.

1346
01:43:30,578 --> 01:43:32,331
Of course you did,
and the law says

1347
01:43:32,456 --> 01:43:34,253
you have the right
to hold a nigger.

1348
01:43:34,417 --> 01:43:36,385
But begging
the law's pardon, it lies.

1349
01:43:37,002 --> 01:43:39,050
Suppose they pass
a law taking away

1350
01:43:39,171 --> 01:43:41,219
your liberty,
making you a slave.

1351
01:43:41,381 --> 01:43:42,507
Suppose.

1352
01:43:42,675 --> 01:43:44,301
That ain't a supposable case.

1353
01:43:44,467 --> 01:43:45,890
Laws change, Epps.

1354
01:43:46,052 --> 01:43:48,146
Universal truths are constant.

1355
01:43:48,305 --> 01:43:51,149
It is a fact,
a plain and simple fact...

1356
01:43:51,307 --> 01:43:54,528
that what is true and right
is true and right for all.

1357
01:43:54,686 --> 01:43:56,689
White and black alike.

1358
01:43:58,314 --> 01:44:00,158
You comparing me
to a nigger, Bass?

1359
01:44:00,317 --> 01:44:03,161
I'm only asking, in the eyes of
God, what is the difference?

1360
01:44:05,155 --> 01:44:06,923
You might as well ask
what the difference is

1361
01:44:06,948 --> 01:44:09,327
between a white man
and a baboon.

1362
01:44:10,536 --> 01:44:13,335
I seen one of them
critters in Orleans.

1363
01:44:13,497 --> 01:44:15,875
Know just as much
as any nigger I got.

1364
01:44:16,167 --> 01:44:17,840
BASS: Listen, Epps.

1365
01:44:18,002 --> 01:44:19,675
These niggers are human beings.

1366
01:44:19,837 --> 01:44:22,197
If they are allowed to climb no
higher than brute animals...

1367
01:44:22,338 --> 01:44:25,012
you and men like you
will have to answer for it.

1368
01:44:26,010 --> 01:44:28,182
There is an ill,
Mr. Epps...

1369
01:44:28,345 --> 01:44:30,722
a fearful ill
resting upon this nation.

1370
01:44:31,347 --> 01:44:34,351
And there will be
a day of reckoning yet.

1371
01:44:36,936 --> 01:44:39,610
You like to hear
yourself talk, Bass...

1372
01:44:39,774 --> 01:44:41,868
better than any man I know of.

1373
01:44:42,943 --> 01:44:46,618
You'd argue that black was
white, or white, black...

1374
01:44:46,780 --> 01:44:49,033
if anybody would contradict you.

1375
01:44:51,034 --> 01:44:54,413
A fine supposition if you lived
among Yankees in New England.

1376
01:44:54,579 --> 01:44:56,252
But you don't.

1377
01:44:59,710 --> 01:45:01,882
You most assuredly do not.

1378
01:45:22,149 --> 01:45:23,570
(EPPS YELLING)

1379
01:45:25,819 --> 01:45:26,945
(LOUD CLATTERING)

1380
01:45:27,404 --> 01:45:29,782
EPPS: I knew it,
I knew it, I knew it!

1381
01:45:32,158 --> 01:45:33,581
Patsey!

1382
01:45:35,578 --> 01:45:36,956
Pats!

1383
01:45:37,664 --> 01:45:39,087
Where is she?

1384
01:45:39,833 --> 01:45:41,256
Where's Pats?

1385
01:45:41,417 --> 01:45:43,761
Where is she, damn it?
Where is she?

1386
01:45:45,713 --> 01:45:48,592
Phebs, where is she? Where is Patsey?
Where is she?

1387
01:45:48,759 --> 01:45:50,055
What you standing there for?

1388
01:45:50,219 --> 01:45:51,458
We know nothing of her, Master.

1389
01:45:51,470 --> 01:45:52,891
Know nothing of what?
We know nothing of...

1390
01:45:53,055 --> 01:45:55,432
Of what?
Where has she gone?

1391
01:45:55,599 --> 01:45:56,600
She run off, ain't she?

1392
01:45:56,766 --> 01:45:57,768
I don't know, Master.

1393
01:45:57,935 --> 01:45:59,481
Where is she?
I don't know, Master.

1394
01:45:59,645 --> 01:46:02,614
You know, you know, you know!

1395
01:46:02,773 --> 01:46:03,614
You know!

1396
01:46:03,774 --> 01:46:05,447
No, I don't! (GROANS)

1397
01:46:05,984 --> 01:46:07,586
(PANTING)

1398
01:46:07,610 --> 01:46:09,658
You miserable black dogs.

1399
01:46:09,822 --> 01:46:12,291
You stand like
the deaf and dumb.

1400
01:46:14,076 --> 01:46:15,453
Speak!

1401
01:46:29,048 --> 01:46:30,609
(SOBBING)

1402
01:46:30,634 --> 01:46:32,306
She gone.

1403
01:46:34,680 --> 01:46:36,648
My Pats is gone.

1404
01:46:53,532 --> 01:46:55,500
Run off?
Run off, did you?

1405
01:46:55,658 --> 01:46:57,658
Master Epps... You miserable wench.
Where you been?

1406
01:46:57,786 --> 01:46:59,162
I been nowhere!

1407
01:46:59,329 --> 01:47:00,421
Lies to your misdeeds!

1408
01:47:00,581 --> 01:47:01,931
The Sabbath day, Master.
I took me

1409
01:47:01,957 --> 01:47:03,309
a walk to commune with the Lord.

1410
01:47:03,333 --> 01:47:04,768
Bring the Lord
into your deceptions?

1411
01:47:04,792 --> 01:47:06,270
You're coming from
Shaw's plantation.

1412
01:47:06,295 --> 01:47:07,591
No!
Master Epps.

1413
01:47:08,130 --> 01:47:09,131
Now, you speak?

1414
01:47:09,297 --> 01:47:11,345
Now that you want to add to her
lies, you find your tongue!

1415
01:47:11,507 --> 01:47:13,819
I went to Master
Shaw's plantation.

1416
01:47:13,844 --> 01:47:15,345
Ah! You admit it.

1417
01:47:15,679 --> 01:47:16,975
Yes, freely.

1418
01:47:17,139 --> 01:47:18,981
And you know why?

1419
01:47:19,140 --> 01:47:21,689
I got this from Mistress Shaw.

1420
01:47:22,185 --> 01:47:26,190
Mistress Epps won't even grant
me no soap to clean with.

1421
01:47:26,774 --> 01:47:30,368
I stink so much,
I make myself gag!

1422
01:47:33,613 --> 01:47:36,868
500 pounds of cotton.

1423
01:47:37,033 --> 01:47:39,036
Day in, day out!

1424
01:47:39,203 --> 01:47:41,046
More than any man here.

1425
01:47:41,204 --> 01:47:43,298
And for that, I will be clean.

1426
01:47:43,457 --> 01:47:45,175
That's all I ask.

1427
01:47:45,333 --> 01:47:48,382
This, here,
what I went to Shaw's for.

1428
01:47:49,837 --> 01:47:50,885
Liar.

1429
01:47:51,047 --> 01:47:54,643
The Lord knows that's all!

1430
01:47:54,801 --> 01:47:55,724
You're a liar.

1431
01:47:55,886 --> 01:47:59,310
And you, blind with
your own covetousness!

1432
01:48:00,181 --> 01:48:02,310
I don't lie, Master.

1433
01:48:02,810 --> 01:48:06,064
If you kill me,
I'll stick to that.

1434
01:48:06,814 --> 01:48:08,407
I'll fetch you down.

1435
01:48:09,233 --> 01:48:11,280
I'll learn you to go to Shaw's.

1436
01:48:11,734 --> 01:48:12,827
Treach.

1437
01:48:14,863 --> 01:48:16,364
Run and fetch some line.

1438
01:48:16,532 --> 01:48:17,703
Edward!

1439
01:48:19,326 --> 01:48:22,329
Strip her. Strike her bare
and lash her to the post.

1440
01:48:27,501 --> 01:48:28,672
(GASPS)

1441
01:48:29,545 --> 01:48:30,921
(SOBBING)

1442
01:48:40,764 --> 01:48:42,908
You done this to yourself, Pats.

1443
01:48:42,932 --> 01:48:44,479
(CONTINUES SOBBING)

1444
01:48:54,610 --> 01:48:55,783
MISTRESS EPPS: Do it.

1445
01:49:00,868 --> 01:49:03,087
Strike the life from her.

1446
01:49:09,292 --> 01:49:10,715
Beat her.

1447
01:49:12,337 --> 01:49:14,590
Give her the whip!
Give it all to her!

1448
01:49:15,882 --> 01:49:18,853
Platt, you come here
and you beat her now.

1449
01:49:21,305 --> 01:49:22,396
Platt!

1450
01:49:25,184 --> 01:49:26,435
Come here!

1451
01:49:28,186 --> 01:49:30,359
PATSEY: I'd rather
it you, Platt!

1452
01:49:31,314 --> 01:49:33,067
You strike her.

1453
01:49:33,942 --> 01:49:35,363
Strike her.

1454
01:49:36,737 --> 01:49:38,363
(PATSEY CONTINUES SOBBING)

1455
01:49:49,582 --> 01:49:51,005
(PATSEY YELLS)

1456
01:49:52,877 --> 01:49:54,175
(PATSEY GROANING)

1457
01:49:57,673 --> 01:49:59,266
He pantomimes.

1458
01:49:59,885 --> 01:50:02,307
There's barely a welt on her.

1459
01:50:02,762 --> 01:50:05,140
That's what your
niggers make of you...

1460
01:50:05,306 --> 01:50:07,479
a fool for the taking.

1461
01:50:11,979 --> 01:50:14,403
EPPS: Strike her, Platt.
Strike her!

1462
01:50:15,692 --> 01:50:16,863
(GROANING)

1463
01:50:31,125 --> 01:50:32,546
You will strike her.

1464
01:50:32,708 --> 01:50:34,426
You will strike
her until her flesh

1465
01:50:34,545 --> 01:50:36,262
is rent and meat and
blood flow equal...

1466
01:50:36,421 --> 01:50:39,220
or I will kill every
nigger in my sight.

1467
01:50:39,382 --> 01:50:40,885
You understand me?

1468
01:50:41,051 --> 01:50:43,895
Strike her! Strike her!

1469
01:50:54,439 --> 01:50:55,907
(PATSEY SCREAMS)

1470
01:50:58,985 --> 01:51:00,658
(PATSEY SOBBING)

1471
01:51:21,507 --> 01:51:23,010
(COUGHING)

1472
01:51:27,139 --> 01:51:29,938
EPPS: Until I say no more.
I ain't said nothing!

1473
01:51:39,859 --> 01:51:41,157
Give me the whip!

1474
01:51:42,154 --> 01:51:43,371
Get up!

1475
01:51:47,826 --> 01:51:49,293
(PATSEY SCREAMING)

1476
01:52:02,798 --> 01:52:04,471
Thou devil!

1477
01:52:07,011 --> 01:52:08,559
Sooner or later...

1478
01:52:09,222 --> 01:52:11,817
somewhere in
the course of eternal

1479
01:52:11,975 --> 01:52:14,569
justice, thou shalt
answer for this sin!

1480
01:52:15,811 --> 01:52:17,314
(PANTING)

1481
01:52:19,983 --> 01:52:23,032
Sin? There is no sin.

1482
01:52:24,488 --> 01:52:27,412
Man does how he pleases
with his property.

1483
01:52:33,037 --> 01:52:36,759
At the moment, Platt,
I'm of great pleasure.

1484
01:52:36,917 --> 01:52:38,760
You be goddamn
careful I don't want to

1485
01:52:38,877 --> 01:52:40,675
come and lighten
my mood no further.

1486
01:53:12,411 --> 01:53:13,707
(GASPS)

1487
01:53:13,869 --> 01:53:15,292
(WHIMPERING)

1488
01:53:20,085 --> 01:53:21,256
(SHOUTS)

1489
01:53:21,877 --> 01:53:23,175
(SOBBING)

1490
01:53:36,600 --> 01:53:38,444
(GASPING IN PAIN)

1491
01:53:49,155 --> 01:53:51,533
(SOBBING)

1492
01:54:58,975 --> 01:55:00,476
Master Bass.

1493
01:55:00,769 --> 01:55:03,943
I want to ask you what part
of the country you come from.

1494
01:55:05,148 --> 01:55:07,024
No part of this land.

1495
01:55:08,109 --> 01:55:10,158
I originate from Canada.

1496
01:55:11,154 --> 01:55:12,701
Now, guess where that is.

1497
01:55:12,863 --> 01:55:14,787
I know where Canada is.

1498
01:55:15,617 --> 01:55:17,368
I've been there myself.

1499
01:55:22,289 --> 01:55:24,132
Montreal...

1500
01:55:24,292 --> 01:55:27,341
and Kingston and Queenston
and a great many places.

1501
01:55:27,503 --> 01:55:29,346
Well-traveled for a slave.

1502
01:55:29,506 --> 01:55:30,552
How came you here?

1503
01:55:32,634 --> 01:55:34,306
Master Bass...

1504
01:55:36,637 --> 01:55:40,016
if justice had been done,
I never would have been here.

1505
01:55:44,813 --> 01:55:46,155
How's this?

1506
01:55:47,189 --> 01:55:48,237
Tell me all.

1507
01:55:53,697 --> 01:55:55,869
I'm afraid to tell you.

1508
01:55:57,533 --> 01:56:00,662
Every word you speak
is a profound secret.

1509
01:56:08,211 --> 01:56:09,884
Your story...

1510
01:56:10,546 --> 01:56:12,015
it is amazing.

1511
01:56:12,173 --> 01:56:14,176
And in no good way.

1512
01:56:16,302 --> 01:56:17,555
(SIGHS)

1513
01:56:18,930 --> 01:56:22,560
Do you believe, sir,
in justice, as you said?

1514
01:56:23,726 --> 01:56:25,274
I do.

1515
01:56:25,436 --> 01:56:29,237
That slavery is an evil
that should befall none?

1516
01:56:32,068 --> 01:56:33,865
I believe so.

1517
01:56:34,029 --> 01:56:35,952
If you truly do...

1518
01:56:37,740 --> 01:56:40,789
then I ask, I beg...

1519
01:56:43,454 --> 01:56:46,253
that you write my friends
in the north...

1520
01:56:46,625 --> 01:56:49,423
acquainting them
of my situation...

1521
01:56:50,795 --> 01:56:55,095
and beseeching them
to forward free papers.

1522
01:57:00,095 --> 01:57:01,769
It would be...

1523
01:57:04,768 --> 01:57:07,612
an unspeakable happiness...

1524
01:57:09,230 --> 01:57:11,279
to see my wife...

1525
01:57:13,777 --> 01:57:16,074
and my family again.

1526
01:57:21,952 --> 01:57:25,331
I traveled this country for
the best part of 20 years...

1527
01:57:25,997 --> 01:57:28,921
and my freedom is everything.

1528
01:57:29,083 --> 01:57:33,430
The fact that I can walk out of here
tomorrow brings me great pleasure.

1529
01:57:36,048 --> 01:57:38,301
My life doesn't
mean much to anyone.

1530
01:57:39,636 --> 01:57:43,310
It seems yours might mean a
lot to a whole lot of people.

1531
01:57:45,057 --> 01:57:49,529
But what you ask of me,
sir, scares me.

1532
01:57:51,689 --> 01:57:54,533
And I must say, I am afraid.

1533
01:57:55,652 --> 01:57:57,996
Not just for you, but for me.

1534
01:58:07,162 --> 01:58:09,336
I will write your letter, sir.

1535
01:58:09,779 --> 01:58:11,100
And if it brings you
your freedom,

1536
01:58:11,126 --> 01:58:12,365
it will be more than a pleasure.

1537
01:58:12,377 --> 01:58:14,345
It will have been my duty.

1538
01:58:14,503 --> 01:58:17,507
Now, would you kindly
hand me those shingles?

1539
02:00:52,078 --> 02:00:53,250
SHERIFF: Platt!

1540
02:00:53,662 --> 02:00:55,711
Where's the boy called Platt?

1541
02:00:59,002 --> 02:01:00,378
Come here, boy.

1542
02:01:22,524 --> 02:01:24,277
Your name is Platt, is it?

1543
02:01:26,069 --> 02:01:27,367
Yes, sir.

1544
